The GC was then analyzed both continuously and categorically, adjusting for age,
race/ethnicity, Gleason score, T stage, margin status, entry PSA, and treatment arm. In
the MVAs, continuous GC was independently associated with DM (HR, 1.17; 95% CI, 1.05-1.32;
P = .006), PCSM (HR, 1.39; 95% CI, 1.20-1.63;
P < .001), and OS (HR, 1.17; 95% CI, 1.06-1.29;
P = .002) (Table
2). The results were similar when GC was analyzed categorically (eTable 2 in
Supplement
2).
